-- JX Raises Full-Year Profit Forecast by 19 Percent on Improved Oil Margins
-- B y   T s u y o s h i   I n a j i m a
-- 2010-11-05T06:58:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-05/jx-japan-s-largest-oil-refiner-increases-full-year-profit-forecast-19-.html
JX Holdings Inc. , Japan’s biggest
refiner, raised its full-year profit forecast by 19 percent as
margins for selling oil products improved after the company was
formed out of a merger.  JX raised its net income forecast for the year to March 31
to 320 billion yen ($4 billion) from 270 billion yen, it said in
a statement today. It increased its sales forecast by 2.5
percent to 9.4 trillion yen.  Net income for the six months to Sept. 30 was 286.7 billion
yen compared with 63 billion yen a year earlier, which
represents the combined profit of Nippon Oil Corp. and Nippon
Mining Holdings Inc. before they merged. The company had sales
of 4.5 trillion yen in the six-month period.  The company’s  shares  rose 2.7 percent today to 496 yen in
Tokyo. JX announced its results after the market closed.  To contact the reporters on this story:
